                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #128v" facs="001 002 130">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), 128v</locus> blank except for pen trials and a few letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#52r" facs="053">Fol. 52r</locus> A mark in red and black ink is set in the margin to mark the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 3–13
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #1v #3v #4r" facs="002 003 005">folss. 1r, 1v, 3v, 4r, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #7v #12r #16r #47r" facs="002 009 013 017 048">1r, 7v, 12r, 16r, 47r, </locus>, etc.) and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴)
                      marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#118v" facs="120"> f. 118v, line 12</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#29v #38r" facs="031 039">29v, 38r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#23r #24v #35v" facs="024 026 037">23r, 24v, 35v</locus>).
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                      completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines
                      to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#20r #51r #53v" facs="021 052 055">fols. 20r, 51r, 53v</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
